	(789,1,'2016-01-14 18:05:50','2016-01-14 18:05:50','<h1 class=\"entry-title\">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>\r\nIf your business requires you to market to building owners or commercial tenants, ProspectNow\'s property ownership lists filtered by predictive analytics will save you time, and make you money. Please review our FAQs below and don\'t hesitate to contact us if you have any additional questions.\r\n<div class=\"peach_background\">\r\n<ul id=\"lstFAQ\">\r\n	<li><a href=\"#Use\">How can I benefit from ProspectNow?</a></li>\r\n        <li><a href=\"#predictive\">How do predictive analytics work to help me find sellers?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#Cost\">How much does it cost?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#trial\">Is there a free trial?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#Property\">What types of properties are covered in the database?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#content\">Where does all this data come from?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#update\">How often do you update your data?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#internet\">What differentiates ProspectNow other real estate data providers?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#compliance\">How can I ensure I am compliant with the federal Do Not Call List?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#sign\">How do I sign up for the service?</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<strong>How can I benefit from ProspectNow?<a id=\"Use\" name=\"Use\"></a></strong>\r\nProspectNow can help you close more deals by providing you a list of properties that are more likely to be listed for sale or to refinance. It is unique in that ProspectNow combines property data, phone numbers and contact management software in a single tool to create the best property ownership database in the industry.Â <a href=\"/commercial-building-owners-demo\">Click here</a>Â to see what you can do with ProspectNow\r\n\r\n<strong>How do predictive analytics work to help me find sellers?</strong><a name=\"predictive\"></a>\r\nProspectNow analyzes thousands of properties that sell each week.  Then we build a profile around the characteristics of the properties that sold.  Then we simply apply our this profile to properties that have yet to sell using a predictive model.  This results in a list of properties with a much higher probability of being listed for sale. \r\n\r\n<strong>How much does it cost?</strong><a name=\"Cost\"></a>\r\nPlans start $89 a month per user for one county and additional counties are $10/mo. Bulk plans are also available that grant nationwide access at discounted rates.\r\n\r\n<strong>Is there a free trial?</strong><a name=\"trial\"></a>\r\nAny potential subscriber is encouraged to create a free account, which will provide access to property ownership lists in the county of their choice. This trial account will showcase the ProspectNow software and search tools, allowing you to see how many property type records are available within your marketplace. Building owner details, however, are only available to paying subscribers or you can also try our free 3 day trial which requires your credit card information. The system will not bill you for 3 days, and if you choose to cancel prior to the end of 3rd day, you will not be billed at all. Otherwise you will be billed every 30 days. Thanks for trying us out!Â <a href=\"/search-commercial-real-estate\">Click here</a>Â to create your free account.\r\n\r\n<strong>What types of properties are covered in the database?</strong><a name=\"Property\"></a>\r\nThe ProspectNow database covers virtually all properties, including, residential, retail, office and industrial property types. The database also contains 30 million business owners and tenants nationwide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Where does all this data come from?</strong><a name=\"content\"></a>\r\nAll property ownership information is public domain, and every county keeps a record of this information for every building within its parameters. Â The challenge many professionals face is that pieces of this information, such as a phone numbers, owner names behind LLCs, and tenants may not be provided in the county records. That\'s where ProspectNow comes in. We do the research for you to find the phone numbers and other information that is absent from county records. Â The resulting property ownership lists are one of the most effective tools you can employ to get more listings.\r\n\r\n<strong>How often do you update your data?</strong>\r\n<a name=\"update\"></a>The ProspectNow database is updated every 30 days. There are a few counties that are updated on an annual basis, but most are updated monthly.\r\n\r\n<strong>What differentiates ProspectNow other real estate data providers?</strong>Â <a name=\"internet\"></a>\r\nProspectNow is designed for commercial and residential real estate professionals. It\'s the only product that integrates phone numbers, property and owner information, LLC data, tenants,Â and a contact manager into one system filtered by predictive analytics. You don\'t have to search through multiple systems to fill in all the information you need on a property. Â Therefore, you can contact more owners in less time, resulting in more deals.\r\n\r\n<strong>How can I ensure I am compliant with the federal Do Not Call List?</strong>Â <a name=\"compliance\"></a>\r\nIf you are only calling businesses, consumers with whom you have an existing relationship, or you are not using ProspectNow for telemarketing at all, then you are exempt from the Do Not Call requirements. Â By default, our phone numbers are <strong>NOT</strong> flagged for the DNC list. Â However, ProspectNow can flag the numbers on the DNC registry if you provide us your Subscription Account Number (SAN). Â Obtaining a SAN is required if you plan to call consumer numbers, and it\'sÂ actually quite easy to setup . Â <a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Get-a-SAN.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Click Here</a> for step-by-step instructions to obtain a SAN. After you have a SAN, login to ProspectNow and under \'My Account\' -&gt; \'DNC Settings\' and submit your SAN. Â Once it\'s approved, you will then be able to see if a number is on the DNC list. Â Remember, lawful use of ProspectNow is a requirement to access the service. Â The Do Not Call registry is constantly changing and while we use best efforts to ensure we are up to date, ultimately you are responsible for compliance.\r\n\r\n<strong>How do I sign up for the service?</strong><a name=\"sign\"></a>\r\nYou can sign up online or by calling 888-956-9998. We accept credit cards or eChecks.<a href=\"/search-commercial-real-estate\">Click Here</a> to sign up','FAQ- property ownership lists','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2016-01-14 18:05:50','2016-01-14 18:05:50','',11,'http://staging.prospectnow.com/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(787,1,'2016-01-14 18:02:31','2016-01-14 18:02:31','<h1 class=\"entry-title\">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>\r\nIf your business requires you to market to building owners or commercial tenants, ProspectNow\'s property ownership lists and tenant data will save you time, and make you money. Please review our FAQs below and don\'t hesitate to contact us if you have any additional questions.\r\n<div class=\"peach_background\">\r\n<ul id=\"lstFAQ\">\r\n	<li><a href=\"#Use\">How can I benefit from ProspectNow?</a></li>\r\n        <li><a href=\"#predictive\">How do predictive analytics work to help me find sellers?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#Cost\">How much does it cost?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#trial\">Is there a free trial?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#Property\">What types of properties are covered in the database?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#content\">Where does all this data come from?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#update\">How often do you update your data?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#internet\">What differentiates ProspectNow from generic list brokers on the Internet?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#compliance\">How can I ensure I am compliant with the federal Do Not Call List?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"#sign\">How do I sign up for the service?</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<strong>How can I benefit from ProspectNow?<a id=\"Use\" name=\"Use\"></a></strong>\r\nProspectNow can help you close more deals by providing you a list of properties that are more likely to be listed for sale or to refinance. It is unique in that ProspectNow combines property data, phone numbers and contact management software in a single tool to create the best property ownership database in the industry.Â <a href=\"/commercial-building-owners-demo\">Click here</a>Â to see what you can do with ProspectNow\r\n\r\n<strong>How do predictive analytics work to help me find sellers?</strong><a name=\"predictive\"></a>\r\nProspectNow analyzes thousands of properties that sell each week.  Then we build a profile around the characteristics of the properties that sold.  Then we simply apply our this profile to properties that have yet to sell using a predictive model.  This results in a list of properties with a much higher probability of being listed for sale. \r\n\r\n<strong>How much does it cost?</strong><a name=\"Cost\"></a>\r\nPlans start $89 a month per user for one county and additional counties are $10/mo. Bulk plans are also available that grant nationwide access at discounted rates.\r\n\r\n<strong>Is there a free trial?</strong><a name=\"trial\"></a>\r\nAny potential subscriber is encouraged to create a free account, which will provide access to property ownership lists in the county of their choice. This trial account will showcase the ProspectNow software and search tools, allowing you to see how many property type records are available within your marketplace. Building owner details, however, are only available to paying subscribers or you can also try our free 3 day trial which requires your credit card information. The system will not bill you for 3 days, and if you choose to cancel prior to the end of 3rd day, you will not be billed at all. Otherwise you will be billed every 30 days. Thanks for trying us out!Â <a href=\"/search-commercial-real-estate\">Click here</a>Â to create your free account.\r\n\r\n<strong>What types of properties are covered in the database?</strong><a name=\"Property\"></a>\r\nThe ProspectNow database covers virtually all properties, including, residential, retail, office and industrial property types. The database also contains 30 million business owners and tenants nationwide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Where does all this data come from?</strong><a name=\"content\"></a>\r\nAll property ownership information is public domain, and every county keeps a record of this information for every building within its parameters. Â The challenge many professionals face is that pieces of this information, such as a phone numbers, owner names behind LLCs, and tenants may not be provided in the county records. That\'s where ProspectNow comes in. We do the research for you to find the phone numbers and other information that is absent from county records. Â The resulting property ownership lists are one of the most effective tools you can employ to get more listings.\r\n\r\n<strong>How often do you update your data?</strong>\r\n<a name=\"update\"></a>The ProspectNow database is updated every 30 days. There are a few counties that are updated on an annual basis, but most are updated monthly.\r\n\r\n<strong>What differentiates ProspectNow other real estate data providers?</strong>Â <a name=\"internet\"></a>\r\nProspectNow is designed for commercial and residential real estate professionals. It\'s the only product that integrates phone numbers, property and owner information, LLC data, tenants,Â and a contact manager into one system filtered by predictive analytics. You don\'t have to search through multiple systems to fill in all the information you need on a property. Â Therefore, you can contact more owners in less time, resulting in more deals.\r\n\r\n<strong>How can I ensure I am compliant with the federal Do Not Call List?</strong>Â <a name=\"compliance\"></a>\r\nIf you are only calling businesses, consumers with whom you have an existing relationship, or you are not using ProspectNow for telemarketing at all, then you are exempt from the Do Not Call requirements. Â By default, our phone numbers are <strong>NOT</strong> flagged for the DNC list. Â However, ProspectNow can flag the numbers on the DNC registry if you provide us your Subscription Account Number (SAN). Â Obtaining a SAN is required if you plan to call consumer numbers, and it\'sÂ actually quite easy to setup . Â <a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Get-a-SAN.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Click Here</a> for step-by-step instructions to obtain a SAN. After you have a SAN, login to ProspectNow and under \'My Account\' -&gt; \'DNC Settings\' and submit your SAN. Â Once it\'s approved, you will then be able to see if a number is on the DNC list. Â Remember, lawful use of ProspectNow is a requirement to access the service. Â The Do Not Call registry is constantly changing and while we use best efforts to ensure we are up to date, ultimately you are responsible for compliance.\r\n\r\n<strong>How do I sign up for the service?</strong><a name=\"sign\"></a>\r\nYou can sign up online or by calling 888-956-9998. We accept credit cards or eChecks.<a href=\"/search-commercial-real-estate\">Click Here</a> to sign up','FAQ- property ownership lists','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2016-01-14 18:02:31','2016-01-14 18:02:31','',11,'http://staging.prospectnow.com/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
